Leading Edge Academy is accepting applications for an Elementary Teacher at our Gilbert Elementary Campus. Must be Highly Qualified. AZ Teacher Certification a plus, but not required. Two or more years classroom teaching experience preferred. AZ State Fingerprint clearance card required. Full time and Part Time opportunities.

The Elementary Teacher position is for the 2020-2021 School Year. Salary is commensurate with experience. Performance bonus available. Benefits available, but not part of the AZ State retirement system.

If you are interested in joining our exceptional professional learning community, please submit the following materials:

✔ Cover letter

✔ Application (Teaching/Professional – downloadable on left column)

✔ Resume

✔ Copy of fingerprint clearance card



(In accordance with Federal law Leading Edge Academy does not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, or disability.)

post_text:
Dear Families,

On Monday, June 29, 2020, Governor Ducey issued an executive order that delays the start of schools until August 17, 2020 due to the current COVID-19 situation. In response to this order, we will be developing a new school calendar that reflects a start date of August 17, 2020. This calendar will be presented to the school boards on July 8, 2020 and will be shared with everyone upon approval by the board.

In addition, the previously scheduled summer school/boot camp that was to begin at campuses next Monday, July 6, 2020, has been cancelled.

As of now, there are no additional changes to our Return to School Plan other than the delay in our start date. However, this is a very fluid situation and information will be provided as we receive it.

Thank you for your continued support of Leading Edge Academy.

Lori Anderson
Executive Director
Lead Charter Schools

post_text: The Summer Food Service Program (SFSP) provides free and healthy meals to youth in Arizona all summer long. Anyone 18 years of age and younger is welcome to receive a meal from a participating summer feeding site. Text the word "FOOD" or "COMIDA" to 877-877 to find meal service sites close to you. Click on the site on the map to get their hours of operation and further info. Have a safe and healthy summer!

post_text:
Sportball AZ is offering free Sportball classes a couple days a week during the Covid-19 restrictions. These classes are fun and interactive for younger students and can be done indoors. This is especially great since the weather has started to heat up.

"Sportball has been teaching Children the fundamentals skills behind sports since 1995. First across North America, and now, Internationally our star program Multi-Sport has put thousands of children on the path to healthy, active living and a life-long love of the sport.
What started with just 3 children and a single location has now grown to 900+ locations across Canada the United States and Singapore. We were one of the first companies to offer developmentally appropriate, non-competitive sports training to Children 12 and under. Today Sportball partners with schools to supplement or enhance existing phys ed programs and with leading research institutions to improve and further develop our curriculum.

At Sportball, we always value positive learning outcomes over winning."

post_text:
Check out this awesome website for some great educational resources as well as books and videos. Normally there is a charge but right now for 30 days it is free!

"Epic! was born out of a single question: How do we make books more accessible to kids? As parents, it always seemed strange to us that our kids could so easily play games and watch videos on their iPhones and iPads, but the same couldn’t be said for books. So in 2013, we decided to build the first “epic” reading experience, designed just for kids. Today, Epic! has grown into an award-winning subscription service, which gives millions of families and classrooms instant, unlimited access to thousands of books, videos and quizzes from leading publishers to help kids everywhere read, learn and grow."

https://www.getepic.com

Here is another great and interesting educational resource.

"From PBS Digital Studios and KQED Education, Above the Noise offers an investigative dive -- albeit a brief one -- into the research behind a variety of popular and newsworthy topics, ranging from technology and climate science to free speech, economics, and beyond. Each video dives into a specific, thought-provoking topic, and the channel's sensibilities are right in line with what high school to college-age students are talking about.

Standout Videos:

Is Video Game Addiction Real? -- A discussion of some of the science behind all the reporting on so-called "Video Game Addiction" and "Gaming Disorder."

Can Procrastination Be a Good Thing? -- Explore some academic research behind the question: Why do people procrastinate?

Why Do Our Brains Love Fake News? -- A brief primer on confirmation bias, and whether or not it's something people can actually avoid.

Today's free educational resource comes from Amazon Future Engineer.

"Amazon Future Engineer is providing free access to sponsored computer science courses in the United States, intended for independent learners in grades 6-12 and teachers who are remotely teaching this age group. Parents can also access the curriculum. The organization is also offering a virtual robotics program through partners CoderZ with a sequenced course that shows learners how to code; early learners use block-based coding; older learners use text-based coding. And Amazon Future Engineer is providing access to Georgia Tech's EarSketch, a free program that helps students learn to code through music. Grammy-award winning artists Ciara and Common have both provided studio-quality music "stems" that students can remix from home using code."

In these difficult times we would all love a trip to San Diego! While that can't happen right now, we invite you all to go on a virtual field trip with us and check out the animals at the San Diego Zoo.

"For more than a century, people have flocked to the San Diego Zoo to discover animals. The Zoo connects people with wildlife to inspire a passion for nature. Picture the wide-eyed wonder on a child’s face upon meeting a living, breathing giraffe. Or the wonder of encountering a penguin that is looking at you with the same curiosity you have about him. These are the moments that tell the story of the San Diego Zoo and San Diego Zoo Safari Park. It is these connections that spark the desire to protect and save species."

The San Diego Zoo is closed, but they are offering free live camera access to their animal exhibits. Go to their website and enjoy a virtual field trip today!

https://zoo.sandiegozoo.org/live-cams

Today's educational resource is a great tool for students in upper elementary, middle school and high school. It is a website called iCivics that offers educational games and activities with a civics basis.

Dear Leading Edge Academy Parents and Staff,

We have continued to monitor the situation with the COVID-19 virus as it relates to school closures and the safety and welfare of our students and staff remain the priority.

As of today, we have decided to extend our current spring break and keep our schools closed until Monday, March 30, 2020. We will continue to monitor the situation throughout the upcoming weeks to determine if a longer closure is needed.

We appreciate your patience and understanding as we navigate this very fluid situation and we will provide all pertinent updates as we have them. Thank you for your continued support of Leading Edge.

Lori Anderson
Executive Director
Lead Charter Schools
